Backport of GHSA-f4xh-w4cj-qxq8 to langsmith 0.4.37.

Combines two upstream fixes:

  1. 9c5515620f9bfa2145fc65d6f4353c4c8a3e96b6 (CWE-843, in v0.8.18):
     unify and harden the attachment-filesystem guard in client.py. The
     original (tuple, Path) check missed JSON/dict-shaped input (list/str),
     so a crafted attachment whose value was a plain string path could be
     opened from disk and uploaded. Replace the three duplicate, identically-
     broken checks in create_run / multipart_ingest / update_run with a
     single fail-closed helper that keys off the data type (inline bytes
     vs. anything else).

  2. 93f19f317dd37a91d67b662b77691f980e5c56ed (CWE-346, post-v0.8.18):
     allow-list fields accepted from baggage replica updates in run_trees.py.
     A tracing-propagation `baggage` header could inject arbitrary fields
     into a run's `updates` dict (including `attachments`); restrict that
     payload to a fail-closed allow-list `{reroot, metadata, tags}`,
     overridable via the LANGSMITH_BAGGAGE_ALLOWED_UPDATE_FIELDS env var.
     The v0.4.37 line lacks the `_filter_replica_for_headers` wrapper
     introduced in v0.6.4, so the sanitizer is applied directly at the
     legacy-format `WriteReplica(...)` conversion site in `_Baggage.from_header`.

Tests are adapted from the upstream commits and reference only symbols that
exist in v0.4.37.

Origin: upstream, https://github.com/langchain-ai/langsmith-sdk/commit/9c5515620f9bfa2145fc65d6f4353c4c8a3e96b6
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/langchain-ai/langsmith-sdk/commit/93f19f317dd37a91d67b662b77691f980e5c56ed
Bug: https://github.com/langchain-ai/langsmith-sdk/security/advisories/GHSA-f4xh-w4cj-qxq8

NOTE: the run_trees.py / test_run_trees.py hunks below are rebased on top of
the already-applied CVE-2026-25528 patch (both touch overlapping baggage-
replica handling in this version); client.py and test_client.py are untouched
by CVE-2026-25528 and keep their original hunks.

